
[1]valuation

   VALUA'TION, n. [from value.]

   1. The act of estimating the value or worth; the act of setting a
   price; as the just valuation of civil and religious privileges.

   2. Apprizement; as a valuation of lands for the purpose of taxation.

   3. Value set upon a thing; estimated worth.

   So slight a valuation.
